The theoretical equation for this is given
here for phase-FZPs, where nu is the ratio

319
00:33:09,510 --> 00:33:19,930
between the absorption index beta and refractive-index
decrement delta and phi - 2 pi delta t/lambda

320
00:33:19,930 --> 00:33:27,520
is the phase shift induced by the x-rays passing
through a ring of thickness t.

321
00:33:27,520 --> 00:33:32,890
The actually achieved efficient is in general
lower than this, as this equation has assumed

322
00:33:32,890 --> 00:33:37,720
